>  Can I use DES without having to pay royalties/licensing fees, etc, if I
>impliment the code myself?  

Yes, just don't export it outside of the US (well, Canada is okay) or
you'll be dealing with ITAR (International Trade in Arms Regulations).

>  And along those lines, is there validation data I can use to see if my
>implimentation of DES is 'up to spec'?
Why not just pick up one of many fine copies off the Net?  Why bother
rewriting it again?

